Bally Manufacturing Corp said it filed ashelf registration with the Securities and Exchange Commissionfor a secondary public offering of two mln shares of Series Dconvertible exchangeable preferred stock.    The stock is exchangeable at Bally's option into thecompany's convertible debentures due February one 2007 and isconvertible at the holder's option into shares of Bally common.The preferred stock carry a liquidation value of 50 dlrs ashare.    All of the shares are being offered by holders of Bally whobought the preferred stock in a private placement in February1987. Bally will not receive any proceeds of the offering, itsaid. Reuter&#3;